defaultValue.description:
The initial value of the text field. This will be used when the component
is used in uncontrolled mode.
defaultValue.name: defaultValue

disabled.description: Whether or not the text field is disabled.
disabled.name: disabled

leadingContent.description: The leading content for the text field.
leadingContent.name: leadingContent

label.description: The label for the text field.
label.name: label

maxLength.description:
Maximum allowed characters for the input. Setting -1 indicates that there is no
limit.
maxLength.name: maxLength

minLength.description:
Minimum allowed characters for the input. Setting -1 indicates that there is no
limit.
minLength.name: minLength

name.description: The name of the text-field, used when submitting an HTML form. See [MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input#htmlattrdefname).
name.name: name

prefixText.description: Text that needs to be used as prefix for the text field.
prefixText.name: prefixText

readonly.description: Whether or not the text field is readonly.
readonly.name: readonly

status.description: The status of the text field.
status.name: status

suffixText.description: Text that needs to be used as suffix for the text field.
suffixText.name: suffixText

supportingText.description:
The supporting text for the text field. Use this to provide additional information
about the text field.
supportingText.name: supportingText

trailingContent.description: The trailing content for the text field.
trailingContent.name: trailingContent

value.description:
The value of the text field. This will be used when the component is used in
controlled mode.
value.name: value

variant.description: The variant of the text field.
variant.name: variant

onChange.description: The callback to call when the value of the text field is committed.
onChange.name: onChange

tags.param: payload The payload containing the previous value and the current value of the component.

onInput.description:
The callback to call when the value of the text field is changed. For controlled components, the
parent component should hook to this event and push back the value.
onInput.name: onInput

tags.param: payload The payload containing the previous value and the current value of the component.
